com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.engine

Interface SpenControlListener


  • public interface SpenControlListener
    The listener interface for callbacks that are called about the state of control on view.
    Since:
    3.0.0

    • Field Summary

      static int PRESS_TYPE_NONE
      No press.

      Tapping on the view.

      • onClosed

        boolean onClosed(ArrayList<SpenObjectBase> objectList)
        This handler is called when control is closed
        Parameters:
        objectList - List of selected object
        Returns:
        true if control is closed successfully, false otherwise.

      • onCreated

                  ArrayList<Rect> relativeRectList,

                  int pressType,
                  PointF point)
        This handler is called when control is created.
        Parameters:
        objectList - List of selected object
        relativeRectList - List of relative rectangle of selected objects
        menu - List of menu item
        styleList - List of control style
        pressType - Type of press
        point - Point of control list

        Since:
        3.0.0

      • onRectChanged

        void onRectChanged(RectF rect,
                   SpenObjectBase object)
        This handler is called when object rect is changed.

        Remarks:
        onObjectChanged(ArrayList) is called when touch action is finished, but onRectChanged(RectF, SpenObjectBase) is called in the middle of touch action.
        Parameters:
        rect - Rect of object
        object - Object that is set to control
        Since:
        3.0.0

      • onRotationChanged

        void onRotationChanged(float angle,
                       SpenObjectBase objectBase)
        This handler is called when object rotation is changed.

        Remarks:
        onObjectChanged(ArrayList) is called when touch action is finished, but onRotationChanged(float, SpenObjectBase) is called in the middle of touch action.
        Parameters:
        angle - Rotation angle
        objectBase - Object that is set to control
        Since:
        3.0.0

        Parameters:
        objectList - List of object
        itemId - ID of item
        Returns:
